Reinforced Bed Frame - Heavy metal frame and 12 solid wood slats compose a central "+" structure to offer up to 1000lbs weight capacity. 8 support points make the bed frame more stable but won't scratch the floor.

Noise-Free - Equipped with velcro and EVA mute bars to avoid friction between wooden slats and metal frames, effectively eliminating noise. No squeak and mattresses won't slip away. Providing you with a quiet sleeping night.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality for the price, and easy to assemble
reviews.reviewText: I assembled the bed by myself in about an hour or so and didn't have any difficulty. It's sturdy and I like it a lot, but my memory foam mattress is a little too low and there's a small gap. Easy fix is a box spring so I'll be getting one of those and it will be perfect! I like the charging option because I have limited wall outlets on this side of the room, and the small shelf is really handy too. It looks great, but I do have to watch my kittens around it because they think it makes an excellent scratching post and the fabric snags very easily.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Exactly As Advertised, Pleased with Purchase
reviews.reviewText: It can be incredibly hit or miss buying cheap furniture from anywhere, but when this had free shipping and free returns, I decided to go for it.I'm not very strong but I do have a lot of experience with building furniture myself. It took me 2.5 hours but I'm SO happy with how it came out, including both the outlets on top worked, that it was worth the time investment.It looks good, it works, it is sturdy and I've had it for a few weeks now and I'm loving it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Looks good, sturdiness is acceptable
reviews.reviewText: Charge ports on top work great, though I need my phone to vibrate in my bed to wake me up in the mornings, so the center-mounted charger poses a choking risk to me. I would put the charger on the side to prevent this. The headboard is soft and has a little shelf up top. Assembly was fine, though the instructions were not crystal clear. I’m 275lbs and the thing doesn’t squeak or creak unless there’s significant bouncing or motion on the frame.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Sturdy bed with a modern appeal
reviews.reviewText: I have never purchased furniture on line before, but am so happy I did in this case. The bed arrived nicely packaged, and I watched in amazement as the UPS lady man-handled it up to my door. The box was so heavy that it took the strength of my husband and me to get it to the bedroom. We managed to assemble it together in about two hours or less, and all the parts were there and fit together nicely. Our queen mattress fits perfectly on it. We use it as a guest bed, and I've only slept on it a couple of times, but it felt solid and didn't make any noises when I moved. My husband is a mechanical engineer and he usually has criticisms of products like this, but he had none here! I especially love the USB port in the headboard, which is why I picked this one. It saves our guests from having to find the outlet behind the nightstand to plug in their phone. It comes with a cord that easily reached from behind the bed to behind the nightstand where the outlet is, so all you have to do is plug your phone into the USB port and safely place your phone on the headboard ledge for the night. I ordered the off-white color, and it is true to what was shown; it has a yellow tone rather than a blue or grey tone. It makes a great improvement to our guest room, having replaced a sleigh bed, which took up too much room. This sleek design doesn't waste any space. I highly recommend this purchase.
